summary: This document appears to be an intelligence report compiling open source information about an Epstein associate, including social media posts and flight log references. It mentions a former Ford model living in California who is accused of being part of Epstein's circle and procuring or participating in abuse.

keyFacts: The document references an open source social media thread accusing a former Ford model named 'Kelly', living in California, of being an Epstein associate who procured and participated in abuse.
The thread author claims to have gone to Kelly's house and been yelled at, accusing Kelly of victim-blaming.
The document references another thread claiming to prove conclusively that an individual flew on Epstein's plane, with an article showing they were listed in flight logs.
The intelligence report compiles data from platforms like Twitter (threader.app, twtext.com) and searches in systems like Accurint and Ejustice/NCIC.
